Proud member of <a href=http://www.geocities.com/guild_ebonstorm/>Ebon Storm</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 569<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 3:43:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2364.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning, I'm feeling very drunk and very nostalgic.</span><hr size=1> Nahide:<br>
<br>
I did that at level five.  From Kelethin to Erud, not Halas, but the same principle.  I did all kinds of touristy things in Erud while I was there--sightseeing, mostly.  I didn't speak a word of human then, so it was a very alienating experience, especially once I got to the Qeynos area and the only people who spoke elvish were half-elves who didn't know they could actually speak elvish.<br>
<br>
I did get killed in Kithicor on the way, and in Highpass, too, but I did make it, eventually.  And, huge kudos to Elaira (I still remember her for this), when I got killed in Qeynos while bound in Freeport, at fifth level, she took me to Surefall and bound me there so my stuff wouldn't rot.<br>
<br>
[Edit: I remembered it was Elaira who did that teleport.  Kendara helped me out with something else at about the same time.] <p><center><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/lasgalensig.jpg" border="0"></center>
<b><center>Lasgalen Lothir</center></b>
<i><center>Oakheart of the Conclave of the Righteous</center></i>
<i><center>Warden of Tunare</center></i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 7/21/02 3:23:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulunathreee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lunathreee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 4:14:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2364.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning, I'm feeling very drunk and very nostalgic.</span><hr size=1> i remember my first trip by boat to Faydwer, all alone from Freeport at level 5.<br>
<br>
this was about a year ago, and of course i was just starting out on another server.  my bardling came running up to the entrance of kaladim gawking at the huge stone dwarf over the entrance, pack slung over her back.  <br>
<br>
immediately, a little nekkid dwarf hails me.  so i hailed him back, and said &quot;i am a tourist in your land, and a thirsty one.  could you perhaps show me where i might be able to buy a frosty ale?&quot;<br>
<br>
he proceeded to lead me all around kaladim, showing me its wonders and pointing out the bank, the different guildhalls (he made special note of the orcbelt quest giver) and the nearest tavern.  i ducked inside, ordered a stack of booze, split it into two and slapped half of it up into a trade window for him while thanking him profusely.  <br>
<br>
then i skipped off down the road while he waved goodbye standing under the gigantic dwarf statue.<br>
<br>
*sniffles*<br>
<br>
from that day to my arrival on FV, i've been trying to recapture that feeling.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaroodooger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaroo Dooger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/20/02 4:49:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2364.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning, I'm feeling very drunk and very nostalgic.</span><hr size=1> Doing the Stein quest with about four members of my guild.  This was before Luclin so we actually had to run to the places we needed to get to.  Good thing we were all casters and could gate!  No one in the guild was able to teleport others at the time either.  Only one death (by a griffon in commons) and it took about eight hours to do (I think). <p><BR>Jarroo Dooger<BR>Tinker's Pride<BR>Gnome Cleric of Bristlebane<BR>"I sent my Soul through the Invisible, Some letter of that After-life spell: And by and by my Soul return'd to me, And answer'd: I Myself am Heaven and Hell." - Omar Khayyam</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utrekrider2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>trekrider2001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 8:11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2364.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning, I'm feeling very drunk and very nostalgic.</span><hr size=1> Banu the shaman (Brell), at every new spell rank I'd cast my new dot's on myself and start my stop watch to figure out how long they'd last.<br>
<br>
For my erudite wizard Armus-(2nd character I ever made. Lvl 11, Brell, Aug 1999-he's still there)- Getting lost in Toxx forest at night with only my candle for light (at that point you could barely see 2 feet in front of you. heheh it was awesome!!) Finally figured out how to make med work at level 8 (heheh didn't know you had to train a point in med before it would work.) Banded armor was cool.<br>
<br>
Xakiz-(39 shaman Torv)- Seeing those new freaky looking goblins from the second expansion.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarknar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarknar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 10:17:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2364.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacific.net.sg/~mnemonic/Images/Zark_portrait.gif width=60 height=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning, I'm feeling very drunk and very nostalgic.</span><hr size=1> I think my first EQ moments were probably among the fondest memories.<br>
<br>
(1) Moreth the High Elven Enchanter (my first ever character) was born on Tallon Zek earlier this year when a few friends convinced me to try EQ and asked me to hop on TZ because they thought the server name sounded nice...<br>
<br>
I still remember how moments after Moreth arrived in Felwithe he fell into the moat trying to follow his friends and swam around endlessly until he saw &quot;You have become better at swimming!(7)&quot; and sent my friend a tell &quot;My yellow bar is almost at 0, I'm gonna drown... bye bye...&quot;, then somehow bumped into a ledge and climbed ashore just before my stamina (luck) ran out and rejoicing at how I escaped certain death in a bottomless pond. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Soon after meeting some very friendly Elves and hours after wondering why the nice Troll I just buffed turned on me and killed me, I was introduced to the concept of PvP servers...<br>
<br>
(2) Zarknar (my second and now, only character) rose on Firiona Vie and gave me the chance to finally learn the mechanics of the game and it seemed every moment from there was a memorable one. Mostly because of the people... <br>
<br>
The most memorable would have to be assaulting the Kromdul Fort of Chalp with two good buddies when we hit our 14th season and complaining about how &quot;Taunt&quot; doesn't work until I realized I had to put a point into training it only when I was in my 16th season... Oh.. and how could I forget my first real Roleplaying experience, a little chat with Zildrax.<br>
<br>
Ah.. memories... <p><DIV align=center>
